1
00:00:00,989 --> 00:00:06,109
The Schaff trend cycle (STC) is a forward-looking,
leading indicator that generates faster, more

2
00:00:06,109 --> 00:00:11,719
accurate signals than other indicators, such
as the MACD because it considers both time

3
00:00:11,719 --> 00:00:14,730
(through cycles) and moving averages.

4
00:00:14,730 --> 00:00:19,590
The Schaff trend cycle (STC) is commonly used
to identify market trends and provide buy

5
00:00:19,590 --> 00:00:22,030
and sell signals to traders.

6
00:00:22,030 --> 00:00:27,600
Schaff trend cycle is a type of oscillator
and is based on the assumption that, regardless

7
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:33,860
of time frame, trends accelerate and decelerate
in cyclical patterns.

8
00:00:33,860 --> 00:00:39,320
Many traders are familiar with the MACD charting
tool, which is an indicator that is used to

9
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:44,720
forecast price action and is notorious for
lagging due to its slow responsive signal

10
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:45,720
line.

11
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:50,920
By contrast, STC’s signal line enables it
to detect trends sooner.

12
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:57,680
In fact, it typically identifies up and downtrends
long before MACD indicator.

13
00:00:57,680 --> 00:01:03,680
While the Schaff trend cycle is computed using
the same exponential moving averages as MACD,

14
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:09,369
it adds a novel cycle component to improve
accuracy and reliability.

15
00:01:09,369 --> 00:01:16,700
While MACD is simply computed using a series
of moving average, the cycle aspect of STC

16
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:20,509
is based on time (for example, number of days).

17
00:01:20,509 --> 00:01:27,020
Although STC was developed primarily for currency
markets, it may be effectively employed across

18
00:01:27,020 --> 00:01:28,049
all markets.

19
00:01:28,049 --> 00:01:33,520
It can be applied to intraday charts, such
as five minutes or one hour charts, as well

20
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:37,819
as daily, weekly, or monthly time frames.

21
00:01:37,819 --> 00:01:43,630
What makes this indicator interesting is that
it is a combination of MACD and fast stochastics

22
00:01:43,630 --> 00:01:48,929
with a cycle component and a smoother to capture
market prices more comprehensively.

23
00:01:48,929 --> 00:01:52,679
It’s basically a combination of leading
and lagging indicators.

24
00:01:52,679 --> 00:01:58,270
So let’s discuss the main problems of MACD
and stochastic.

25
00:01:58,270 --> 00:02:04,090
The MACD follows prices with its 12- and 26-period
exponential moving average (EMA) components

26
00:02:04,090 --> 00:02:06,210
and nine-day EMA signal line.

27
00:02:06,210 --> 00:02:09,170
In this capacity, it is a trend indicator.

28
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:14,970
Yet it is lagging because it doesn’t always
lead prices and is prone to false signals

29
00:02:14,970 --> 00:02:17,300
especially in fast-moving markets.

30
00:02:17,300 --> 00:02:24,080
So you have to adjust the settings to satisfy
your price and market objectives.

31
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:26,510
The stochastic is also lagging.

32
00:02:26,510 --> 00:02:31,620
The problem with stochastic is its ability
to generate false signals, while markets can

33
00:02:31,620 --> 00:02:34,540
take off before signals are generated.

34
00:02:34,540 --> 00:02:40,460
Part of the problem with stochastic oscillator
is its concentration on the 3-day simple moving

35
00:02:40,460 --> 00:02:42,840
average as the signal line.

36
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:47,630
False signals and slow reactions are just
the beginning of problems, especially for

37
00:02:47,630 --> 00:02:53,410
short-term and day traders because the three-day
simple moving average is too short a term

38
00:02:53,410 --> 00:02:57,570
to represent fast markets and act as a true
trigger line.

39
00:02:57,570 --> 00:03:03,140
The Schaff trend cycle (STC) indicator tries
to fix these problems by incorporating a shorter-term

40
00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:10,090
EMA set with a default at 23 with a longer-term
EMA with a default at 50.

41
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:13,910
This remedies the MACD and fast stochastic
false signal.

42
00:03:13,910 --> 00:03:18,740
This combination can be employed to capture
trends, but it doesn’t incorporate entries

43
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:20,670
and exits fully.

44
00:03:20,670 --> 00:03:23,430
To fix this, a signal was needed.

45
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:29,380
The MACD’s nine-day exponential signal line
was not always effective, while fast stochastic

46
00:03:29,380 --> 00:03:31,580
%d signal line was also a failure.

47
00:03:31,580 --> 00:03:35,180
You need a true signal that would capture
a true trend.

48
00:03:35,180 --> 00:03:40,570
This came from cycle theory, a theory never
fully incorporated into an indicator.

49
00:03:40,570 --> 00:03:47,670
This signal line was derived from theories
and practices of 10-, 20-, and 40-day currency

50
00:03:47,670 --> 00:03:49,000
cycles.

51
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:56,500
The halfway point between the 23- and 50-day
EMA is, in cycle theory, 10 so the cycle default

52
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:59,160
is set as a standard 10.

53
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:05,130
But this cycle can also be viewed as a halfway
point of a 20-day cycle as well.

54
00:04:05,130 --> 00:04:10,310
This is the signal line that denotes trends,
ranges, or congestion.

55
00:04:10,310 --> 00:04:15,940
The developer of this indicator considered
that currency cycles generally come in 10-,

56
00:04:15,940 --> 00:04:18,459
20-, and 40-day cycles.

57
00:04:18,459 --> 00:04:21,199
These are measured by daily and weekly candlesticks.

58
00:04:21,199 --> 00:04:27,990
In addition, you must know that not all highs
are cycle highs and not all lows are cycle

59
00:04:27,990 --> 00:04:28,990
lows.

60
00:04:28,990 --> 00:04:34,379
One of the problems with the STC indicator
is that the signal line can get stuck in overbought

61
00:04:34,379 --> 00:04:38,030
or oversold territories for extended periods.

62
00:04:38,030 --> 00:04:41,199
This is because cycles haven’t completed
their time.

63
00:04:41,199 --> 00:04:45,479
But, we’ll discuss these problems later.

64
00:04:45,479 --> 00:04:47,199
So how does it work?

65
00:04:47,199 --> 00:04:53,210
The main idea behind this oscillator is to
combine the benefits of trend and cycle indicators

66
00:04:53,210 --> 00:04:57,819
and minimize their drawbacks such as lags
or false signals.

67
00:04:57,819 --> 00:05:03,990
The main goal of the STC is to identify or
confirm price direction and market turning

68
00:05:03,990 --> 00:05:05,099
points.

69
00:05:05,099 --> 00:05:07,449
Here is how to understand its readings.

70
00:05:07,449 --> 00:05:12,349
There are two thresholds: 25 and 75.

71
00:05:12,349 --> 00:05:17,180
When the indicator crosses above the 25 line,
an uptrend is observed.

72
00:05:17,180 --> 00:05:23,610
When the indicator crosses below the 75 line,
a downtrend is believed to be present.

73
00:05:23,610 --> 00:05:29,680
When the indicator is between the 25 and the
75 lines, the trend is developing in one of

74
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:31,660
these two directions.

75
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:37,620
When the indicator turns into a straight line
(which only happens in its uppermost and lowermost

76
00:05:37,620 --> 00:05:44,461
points), the asset is either overbought — when
above the 75 line, or oversold — when below

77
00:05:44,461 --> 00:05:46,850
the 25 line.

78
00:05:46,850 --> 00:05:55,419
In both cases, a trend reversal can be expected,
but no exact time timeline is provided.

79
00:05:55,419 --> 00:05:59,120
How to apply the STC indicator in trading?

80
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:04,740
The Schaff trend cycle (STC) is a pretty straightforward
indicator, as there are not so many ways in

81
00:06:04,740 --> 00:06:06,740
which it can be used.

82
00:06:06,740 --> 00:06:12,349
And remember, though originally designed for
forex trading, it can be effectively applied

83
00:06:12,349 --> 00:06:15,550
to all asset types and on all time frames.

84
00:06:15,550 --> 00:06:19,689
Here’s how traders usually use Schaff trend
cycle.

85
00:06:19,689 --> 00:06:25,009
When the indicator goes above the 25 line,
the trend is believed to be taking a positive

86
00:06:25,009 --> 00:06:27,380
turn (according to the indicator).

87
00:06:27,380 --> 00:06:32,900
It is when traders consider opening a buy
position, but only if the confirmation is

88
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:33,990
received.

89
00:06:33,990 --> 00:06:39,120
For example, a candle after current one that
moves in the same direction can be considered

90
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:40,680
a confirmation.

91
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:48,090
Readings of other indicators that go in line
with STC can also be treated as a confirmation.

92
00:06:48,090 --> 00:06:51,349
The same rules apply to negative trends.

93
00:06:51,349 --> 00:06:57,009
When the indicator goes below the 75, some
traders consider opening a sell position,

94
00:06:57,009 --> 00:06:58,870
of course with confirmation.

95
00:06:58,870 --> 00:07:05,039
STC is a leading indicator, which means that
it sends a signal before the price move has

96
00:07:05,039 --> 00:07:06,080
occurred.

97
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:12,410
It also means that it lacks the accuracy of
lagging indicators and should be used in conjunction

98
00:07:12,410 --> 00:07:15,830
with other technical analysis tools, never
on its own.

99
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:21,949
So, buy and sell signals are generated when
the signal line breaches 25 at the bottom

100
00:07:21,949 --> 00:07:24,610
and 75 at the top.

101
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:30,749
When the signal line breaches 25 and is heading
up, this is a possible buy, or a long position,

102
00:07:30,749 --> 00:07:36,339
when the signal line breaches 75 and is pointing
down, this is a potential short.

103
00:07:36,339 --> 00:07:42,430
One exit possibility is when the short trade
hits the bottom and breaches the 25 level

104
00:07:42,430 --> 00:07:47,360
and when the long trade hits the top and breaches
75 level.

105
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:51,949
But if the signal line is pointing in the
right direction, you may choose to stay in

106
00:07:51,949 --> 00:07:58,789
the trade since currencies can easily trend
to the high 90 level at the top and near zero

107
00:07:58,789 --> 00:08:00,059
at the bottom.

108
00:08:00,059 --> 00:08:04,900
It is a good idea to find confirmation through
candles.

109
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:10,039
Before the long position, make sure you have
an upward candle and a downward candle for

110
00:08:10,039 --> 00:08:11,039
shorts.

111
00:08:11,039 --> 00:08:16,020
Doug Schaff, the developer of the indicator,
recommended a confirmation by entering on

112
00:08:16,020 --> 00:08:22,120
the second candle up for longs and the second
candle down for shorts.

113
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:27,139
Simple price action, like paying attention
at market swings like higher highs and higher

114
00:08:27,139 --> 00:08:29,710
lows are even better.

115
00:08:29,710 --> 00:08:36,380
Looking at this Tesla chart, we can first
apply the trend filter, in this case an uptrend,

116
00:08:36,380 --> 00:08:41,900
and look to take only buy signals, when the
indicator breaches 25.

117
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:47,050
We had some decent signals just by paying
attention to the main trend.

118
00:08:47,050 --> 00:08:48,350
The same for a downtrend.

119
00:08:48,350 --> 00:08:56,610
We have lower lows and lower highs, so we
take only shorts when the STC crosses below

120
00:08:56,610 --> 00:08:58,019
75.

121
00:08:58,019 --> 00:09:17,779
Here are a few trade examples using Schaff
trend cycle indicator.

122
00:09:17,779 --> 00:09:21,279
Settings can be adjusted according to various
time frames.

123
00:09:21,279 --> 00:09:28,029
For example, Schaff recommended you try smaller
EMAs for longer time frames and longer EMAs

124
00:09:28,029 --> 00:09:29,860
for shorter time frames.

125
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:35,300
The smaller the number used for cycles, the
more turns you will witness while the higher

126
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:40,230
numbers will forecast fewer turns with more
cycle accuracy.

127
00:09:40,230 --> 00:09:45,790
What you want from adjustments is for the
signal line to perfectly follow prices and

128
00:09:45,790 --> 00:09:47,290
candles.

129
00:09:47,290 --> 00:09:52,280
While I find this indicator to be reliable
when the signal is caught correctly, there

130
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:53,759
is one problem.

131
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:58,930
The signal can stay in overbought or oversold
conditions for extended periods.

132
00:09:58,930 --> 00:10:04,321
So you need to have an alternative exit plan,
maybe a trailing stop, or a fib target, to

133
00:10:04,321 --> 00:10:07,680
get the most profit out of your trade.

134
